Author: James Keesey
Name: Chatter
Description: Allows for saving char conversations, separated by groups of people and chat types.
Punchline: Saves and filters chats.

Author: kelvin124124
Name: CopyTranslated
Description: Copy translated item name by right-clicking.
Punchline: Copy translated item name by right-clicking.

Author: NotNite, lostkagamine, guyven
Name: Linkpearl
Description:
An actually updated Mumble positional audio plugin. Because people still use Mumble... right?
Enable "Link to Game and Transmit Position" and the Link plugin in your Mumble settings. Do NOT enable the Final Fantasy XIV plugin - it's unrelated to Linkpearl.
Punchline: An actually updated Mumble positional audio plugin

Author: Haselnussbomber
Name: MogMogCheck
Description: MogMogCheck is a small plugin to assist you in tracking the rewards of the Moogle Treasure Trove event (called Mog Mog Kollektion in German, hence the name).
Punchline: Tracking assistant for Moogle Treasure Trove rewards.

Author: VariableVixen
Name: Positional Assistant
Description: If you have a hard time telling whether you're in the right spot for positional attacks, this plugin can draw guidelines on your screen to help you tell where you need to be.
Punchline: Never guess whether you'll make that positional again!

Author: isaiahcat
Name: Quest Tracker
Description: Easily track quest completion
Punchline: For the quest completionist

Author: MidoriKami
Name: Who am I again?
Description: Shows who you are in the server info bar.
Punchline: Ever forget who you are? We can fix that!

Author: Anna
Name: XIVChat Server
Description:
XIVChat is a suite of software allowing you to use FFXIV's chat from
different devices. This is the server component required to do so.

For information about clients to use with this server, see the website.
Punchline: Use chat away from the game.

Author: Lynie
Name: Absolute Roleplay
Description: Allows users to create, manage, view and bookmark roleplay profiles with FF.
Punchline: A plugin for creating profiles and sharing them, with more to come!

Author: Glyceri
Name: Acquisition Date
Description:
Shows the date when you acquired:
- Achievements
- Quests
- Duties
- Levels
- Fish
- Sightseeing Log Entries
- Glasses
- Minions
- Mounts
- Orchestrion Rolls
- Fashion Accessories
And More!
Punchline: Shows the date when you acquired something.

Author: Cytraen, yomishino
Name: Aether Compass
Description:
This plugin detects certain objects/NPCs such as Aether Currents nearby and shows where they are by various ways, e.g. pointing to their locations on screen and notifying you in Chat.

Currently detects:
	- Aether Currents
	- Eureka Elementals (by apetih)
	- Mob Hunt Elite Marks
	- Gathering Points
	- [Experimental] Island Sanctuary Gathering Objects and Animals
	- [Experimental] Quest-related NPCs/Objects 

Note: Because most objects/NPCs are not loaded when they are too faraway or when there are too many entities nearby (such as too many player characters), they will not be detected in this case.

Icon by Lumas Arkfrost
Punchline: Compasses that detect and mark certain nearby objects/NPCs

Author: wompscode
Name: AFKMute
Description: Mutes your game when you're AFK. /afkmute to toggle.
Punchline: Mutes your game when you're AFK.

Author: Critical_Impact
Name: Allagan Item Search
Description: Allagan Item Search is a dalamud plugin designed to help you search and filter all the items available in the game.
Punchline: Trying to find that item you don't know the name of? Maybe Allagan Item Search can help.

Author: Critical_Impact
Name: Allagan Market
Description:
Allagan Market's primary purpose is to provide a list of all retainer listings/sales across all characters.

It'll do it's best to track your sales but it works best when it's always on!
Punchline: Get your retainer sales organized, track active sales, historical sales and undercutting!

Author: Sohtoren
Name: Altoholic
Description: Get gils, currencies, inventory and retainers items from all your characters
Punchline: Informations about your alts

Author: silasary
Name: ArchipelagoXIV
Description: Key Item Randomizer for FFIXV
Punchline: Client for the Archipelago Multiworld Randomizer.

Author: UnknownX
Name: A Realm Recorded
Description: Adds additional features to the duty recorder and automatically starts it in most instances.
Punchline: Allows you to use the duty recorder

Author: Gotest
Name: Audible Character Status
Description:
Plays a sound for certain statuses of the player. Such as low HP or MP.
You will need to provide your own sound files.
Punchline: You like annoying low HP sounds? This is great for you!

Author: Rietty
Name: AutoMammet
Description: Provides an easy copy and pastable CSV format you can use for island sanctuary spreadsheets. Provides options to export the popularity, future popularity and the current cycle's demand and shift values. Both as words and as numbers on a scale of -2 to 2. This plugin does not provide any calculations for Island Sanctuary, merely an export option for your ingame data.
Punchline: Provides an easy copy and pastable CSV format you can use for island sanctuary spreadsheets.

Author: VariableVixen
Name: AutoMountBgm
Description: Some mounts have really cool BGM tracks (Cruise Chaser FTW) while others are almost sickening in how much you hear them. It's annoying to keep needing to use /mountbgm, but now you won't have to - just let the plugin do it for you!
Punchline: Automatically control mount BGM for individual mounts!

Author: zhudotexe
Name: PaissaHouse
Description:
Looking for that perfect house? PaissaHouse lets you receive notifications when a new plot of land is up for sale on your home world.
View the list of all houses available on a world at https://paissadb.zhu.codes/!

Want to contribute? Check out the repository (globe icon below) for instructions.
Punchline: Crowdsourced housing alerts and lottery tracking for all.

Author: Aly
Name: AutoTimer
Description: Auto-Attack Timer Bar based on the Triggernometry trigger by aya liz.
Punchline: Auto-Attack Timer Bar.

Author: NeNeppie
Name: Avant-Garde
Description:
This plugin is a crowdsourced project, aiming to provide a comprehensive list for all hint categories.
See the github page for information on how you can contribute.
Punchline: Displays a list of valid gear pieces beside hints in the Fashion Report minigame.

Author: Mienna
Name: Beachcomber
Description:
This solver examines your Island Sanctuary data (including your Isleventory!) to provide recommendations to maximize your Seafarer's Cowrie earnings.

Made in collaboration with the Overseas Casuals.
Punchline: Determines the most profitable agenda for your Island Sanctuary workshop each cycle

Author: Infi, ash, Anna
Name: Better Party Finder
Description:
Filter the party finder better.

All vanilla filtering is available, plus:

- Create filter presets to easily switch between
- Whitelist/blacklist specific duties and categories
- Add character names to hide PFs from
- Remove PFs above maximum item level
- Filter on item level range
- Filter on multiple jobs and slots (ex. MCH + GNB available)
Punchline: Use advanced Party Finder filter presets.

Author: Infi
Name: Better Playtime
Description:
Provides expanded functionality to seamlessly track total playtime.
Requires only using /playtime once on each character (again to refresh the time),

- Supports multiple characters,
- Customisable output formats such as hours or minutes
Punchline: Ever wanted detailed information on your playtime all the way down to the second?

Author: Lynesth
Name: Better Targeting System
Description: A more intelligent targeting system for the game which also includes new keybinds.
Punchline: A more intelligent targeting system for the game.

Author: Elypha
Name: BilingualTooltips
Description:
Yes, we have tooltips displayed in two languages now. You paid SE for 4 languages so make good use of it.

- Wanna know and learn how that item is written in another language? - No problem.
- Got fed up of カタカナ and would rather read the English words? - We've got you.
Punchline: In case the WoL speaks more than one language

Author: Lily
Name: BISBuddy
Description:
Highlights gear, coffers, and materia needed for all your gearsets. Imports directly from Etro or Xivgear for frictionless setup.

Highlights items needed for gearsets on:
    - Need/Greed Loot Windows
    - NPC Shops and Exchanges
    - Marketboard
    - Player Inventories
    - Item Tooltips

When melding materia, highlights:
    - Items to meld
    - Materia to meld to item

Automatically syncs gearsets with player inventory
Punchline: Gearing, streamlined.

Author: Infi, Sl0nderman
Name: Blue Mage Helper
Description: Adds monster names and coordinates to the "Where to Learn" section of your blue mage spellbook.
Punchline: Helps you fill out your Blue Mage Spellbook

Author: K-Cli
Name: Bozja Buddy
Description:
Features:
• Resistance relic guide and tracking.
• Info about Lost Actions, Fragments, FATEs/CE, Field Notes e.g. location, drops, marketboard price, fate chains, mettle rewards, exp rewards, etc.
• Node graph viewer.
• Weather forecast.
• Alarms based on time, weather, and FATE/CE.
• Custom loadouts planning, saving, and sharing. Featuring recommended loadouts from many communities.
• Overlay for Lost Find Cache. Filterable by name, role, fragment, weight, and Custom Loadout of choice.
• View Bozja stats and Cache from anywhere. Customisable alert for actions that are running low.
• Delubrum Reginae (Savage) resources and communities.
Punchline: Improve your Bozja sufferring. Maybe.

Author: NeNeppie
Name: Lights, Camera, Action!
Description: This plugin lets you save unlimited camera & lighting configurations/presets in Group Pose at a time, vastly improving over the vanilla feature which lets you save only one of each.
Punchline: Save and load unlimited camera and lighting presets in Group Pose

Author: Nagi'to Atreides
Name: Casexile
Description: Lets you use any in-game slash command without worrying about capitalization. Whether you type "/action", "/ACTION", "/AcTiOn" or any variation thereof, the plugin ensures the intended action takes place without wasting your time.
Punchline: Case-Insensitive Slash Commands

Author: Anya Hichu
Name: ChatContext
Description: Add sender target name in chat messages and displays nearly player targets
Punchline: Add sender target name in chat messages.

Author: Arrest Everybody
Name: ChatEmoteColor
Description: A simple plugin that recolors emote chat lines depending on who is executing the emote and their target.
Punchline: Recolors emote lines in chat.

Author: iv230
Name: Chat Proximity
Description: This plugin will change message in the chat within the "say" channel, darkening people when they're far from you.
Punchline: Know how far they talk from.

Author: Infi, Anna
Name: Chat 2
Description:
Chat 2 is a complete rewrite of the in-game chat window as a plugin.
It supports:

- Unlimited tabs
- Tabs that always send to a certain channel
- More flexible filtering
- RGB channel colouring
- Completely variable font size
- Sidebar tabs
- Unread counts
- Screenshot mode (obfuscate names)
Punchline: Electric Boogaloo - ♪ A whole new chat, a new fantastic chat window ♪

Author: MidoriKami
Name: Chill Frames
Description: Tired of your GPU melting your face off while just running around? Why render at 240 FPS when you're just staring at that gathering node? Fret no more! Chill Frames allows you to limit the games framerate while out of combat!
Punchline: Limit Framerate while out of combat

Author: Guerzoniansus, Karou
Name: Clean Hunt Chat
Description:
Hides shouts and yells, unless they contain flag coordinates or 'switching instance' messages.
Use /cleanhunt to turn on for a configurable amount of time (default 1 hour).
Use /cleanhunt off to disable early.
Punchline:
No more cringe during hunt trains.
Temporarily filters away Shouts and Yells that don't contain a flag or an instance message.

Author: Aelexe
Name: Coin Pouch
Description: Currency alerts and convenient teleports.
Punchline: Currency alerts and convenient teleports.
Changelog:
Release v0.0.1.1
-- Features
- Updated for Dalamud API 7
- Updated currencies and currency caps for patch 6.2

Author: Seventh
Name: Collections
Description:
Collections provides an interface to track, discover and interact with your Collections in game.
Integrates with Glamour systems (Preview, Create Sets, Glamour Plates).
Supports: Glamour, Mounts, Minions, Emotes, Hairstyles, Triple Triad, Blue Mage, Bardings, Framer Kits, Orchestrions, Outfits, Fashion Accessories, Facewear.
Punchline: Track, Discover and Interact with your Collections in game

Author: foophoof
Name: Collector's Anxiety
Description: Collector's Anxiety helps completionists or players with a hobby for collecting in-game things keep track of what they do or don't have in an easy-to-use checklist format. Data is loaded live from the game, so collection statuses are updated in real-time.
Punchline: Hey guys, Famous YouTuber here. Do you ever get Collector's Anxiety?

Author: TheThirdDoor
Name: Conditional Tweaks
Description:
Lets the user change game settings based on the character's state.
Do you want to keep you weapon out in dungeons?
Do you want BGM to always be on for cutscenes?
Do you want the world to turn purple when you jump?
Then this is the plugin for you!

 In fact here are the rules you'll need for that last thing (copy and import them one at a time).
Rule(Miounne's standard directive | AccessibilityColorBlindFilterEnable 1/0 conditions({Jumping, True} ))
Rule(Kan-E-Senna's shoddy golden rule | AccessibilityColorBlindFilterType 3/0 conditions({Jumping, True} ))

Not available in pvp.
Punchline: Tweaks and options based on the charactor's state.

Author: Berna
Name: Congratulations
Description:
Get aurally rewarded when you get commended on duties.

Comes with default sounds for when you get commended by 1/3, 2/3, 3/3 or all seven members of the duty you were in, but you can set custom sounds for each type of trigger by opening /congratsconfig.

The fractioned values are in relation to how many of those members could commend you (i.e. excluding those that were in your party before joining the duty).
Punchline: Get aurally rewarded when you get commended on duties.

Author: Due
Name: ContactsTracker
Description:
Remember to change setting according to your need.
Use the Settings button to enter analyze window.
Punchline: Help you record duty and who you met.

Author: zw3lf
Name: Coordinate Importer
Description: Import map coordinates from various sources (e.g. Siren Hunts or Bear Toolkit) and dump them into echo chat. Use /ci to open the dialog box.
Punchline: Import map coordinates to echo chat.

Author: Asriel
Name: Craftimizer
Description: Allows you to generate macros and simulate all sorts of crafts without having to open another app. Open your crafting log to get started!
Punchline: Simulate crafts, create computer-assisted macros, and get mid-craft suggestions from the comfort of your own game!

Author: Koizumi
Name: Craft Remaining
Description: A simple plugin that displays how much progress and quality is remaining for your craft, without having to do the maths! Great to use in conjunction with Calculations or SimpleTweaks Improved Crafter Tooltips.
Punchline: A simple plugin that displays how much progress and quality is remaining for your craft.

Author: ItsBexy
Name: CrossUp
Description:
This plugin provides various customizations for the look and feel of the Cross Hotbar.

-Split up the left/right hotbars
-Display Expanded Hold Controls Separately
-Customize colors and element positions
-Greater control over which sets your extra bars are mapped to
Punchline: Customize the Cross Hotbar!

Author: MidoriKami, Lharz
Name: CurrencyAlert
Description: This plugin lets you easily manage your various currencies to prevent from wasting precious resources.
Punchline: Display alerts upon reaching configurable currencies thresholds.

Author: Blackcatz1911
Name: Currency Spender
Description: Never wonder 'What should I do with this?' again. Access real-time prices from Universalis, identify missing collectibles tied to your currencies, and unlock new possibilities for utilizing your in-game resources effectively.
Punchline: Discover how to use all the in-game currencies.

Author: 0x0ade
Name: CustomResolution
Description: Basic plugin that allows you to specify a custom resolution.
Punchline: Enforces a custom resolution for the game, similar to NVIDIA DSR.

Author: radax864
Name: CWLSLastSeenTool
Description: A tool for tracking when CWLS members were last seen online. /cwlslst to open the tool.
Punchline: A tool for tracking when CWLS members were last seen online.

Author: Munn
Name: DaCoblyn
Description: Translate tools that allow you to communicate with foreign friend that you doesn't know what they're saying.
Punchline: Speak to your Japanese friend!

Author: MidoriKami
Name: DailyDuty
Description: Automatically track and complete many daily and weekly tasks.
Punchline: Easily Track Daily and Weekly tasks

Author: Infi
Name: Death Roll Helper
Description:
Plugin to help with a number of /random and /dice related games.

Venue Mode:
    + Concise display of all concurrent players in a list-based format
    + Includes functionality for Truth or Dare and Giveaway modes 
    + Support for multiple sorting types (min, max, nearest to) 
    + Highlight numbers based on regex matching 
Death Roll Mode:
    + Support for multiple players
    + Automatically checks for correct number ranges from each player
Tournament Mode:
    + 1 vs 1 Death Roll Tournament
    + Automatic bracket generation
    + Uneven number of players get filled with byes
    + Randomization via shuffling is enforced
    + Forfeit functionality if a player needs to leave
Blackjack:
	+ Support for all normal moves
    + Automatic reward calculation based on standard rules
    + Simplistic, visual view of cards in play
    + Automatic drawing of cards, or manual player based roll for cards
    + Current players can be seemlessly moved to subsequent rounds
    + Further support for custom rules is planned (For example, the dealer can hit above 16)

Features:
    + Can block or prevent players from partaking in any of your games 
    + Accept only /random or /dice commands
    + Ease of removing players from partaking in the concurrent game/tournament

Includes language support for English, German and French FFXIV clients. (Japanese support is planned)
More features are planned for future updates in accordance with feedback.
Punchline: Plugin to help with a number of /random and /dice related games.

Author: Infi, mudcrab2142
Name: Diadem Calculator
Description: Calculates your current sessions points and scrip reward
Punchline: Yet another useful calculator~

Author: herulume, sevii
Name: Directional
Description: Draw the compass directionals around the target (boss relative or true north)
Punchline: Draw the compass directionals around the target for easier callouts

Author: PunishedPineapple
Name: Distance
Description:
Displays the distance in yalms to your target and/or other enemies, players, NPCs, etc.  It can also display the aggro range for supported bosses.
Please note that this plugin automatically downloads updates for aggro data by default.  This can be disabled in the plugin settings if you wish.
Punchline: Target distance widgets.

Author: Noevain
Name: Dot Calculator
Description: Show as FlyText or chat prints how much damage the current DoT you have put on the target has dealt
Punchline: Show how much damage your DoTs have dealt so far

Author: dechamps-chen
Name: Dot Position
Description: Dot Position adds a simple, customizable marker under your character to show your precise hitbox location.
Punchline: "See exactly where you stand."

Author: MorCherlf
Name: DutyPusher
Description: You can use this plugin to push notify to your device when your duty is ready
Punchline: Push notify to your device when your duty is ready

Author: Eidolon
Name: Dynamic UI Scaling
Description: Automatically finely scales the game UI by resolution.
Punchline: Automatically finely scales the game UI by resolution.

Author: Olaren
Name: Easy Translate
Description: Search anything and get the translations in other languages. Use /et to open the ui
Punchline: Translate anything!

Author: Infi
Name: Eventy
Description:
Simple but useful calender
- Current events displayed within a server bar entry for quick viewing
- Browse through current, upcoming and previously held events
- Special dates for Liveletters and other important occasions are highlighted
Punchline: Never forget a seasonal event ever again

Author: Critical-Impact
Name: Fantasy Player
Description:
Control Spotify playback from within FFX|V
Use the button below to open settings or use the '/pfp settings' command.
Originally by BiscuitUmU
Localization by Dormanil
Punchline: Like you'd ever be sick of the in game music right?

Author: Meoiswa
Name: Fast Job Switcher
Description: Enables the player to switch jobs using their three letter acronyms as commands. (*: five or more)
Punchline: Always five* keystrokes away from any job

Author: SamuelSapp
Name: Fast Waymarks
Description: Fast waymarks with settings for common configurations. Rotate and resize with a handy preview window.
Punchline: For when you want to spend time fighting the boss, not fiddling with waymarks.

Author: CFG
Name: FC Name Color
Description:
Color your FC’s tag or the entire nameplate if they are in your FC or other specified FCs.
Works using Lodestone data, so it can continue working inside duties as well as on different servers!
Punchline: Color your FC member’s FC tags
FeedbackMessage: Please include your character’s name and server if you’re reporting a bug or issue. This helps a lot with the troubleshooting process.

Author: Cometo
Name: Gamba
Description:
A simple plugin for casino dealers to easily manage all their player's bets and 
quickly getting the payout of each round to keep the gambing going.
Punchline: Let's go gambling!

Author: ItsBexy
Name: Gauge-O-Matic
Description: Gauge-O-Matic allows you to customize your job gauges by adding extra counters, bars, and indicators in a variety of styles
Punchline: Enhance and customize job gauges.

Author: Chivalrik
Name: GentleTouch
Description:
You need to configure patterns and triggers before it will work, 
open the configuration window to do that. 
DS5 is currently unsupported. 
Currently supported triggers are:
- Cooldowns
- Near Aether Current
Punchline: Create vibration patterns for the controller and specify triggers to make it vibrate.
Changelog:
- feat: DualSense support via DS4 compatibility vibrations
- feat(DualSense): Set resistance for Adaptive Triggers
- feat(DS+DS4): Two extra macro buttons:
  Create (DualSense) / TouchPad (DualShock4) as Individual Macro #96,
  PS Button as Individual Macro #97
- feat: Option to /draw & /sheathe with PS button instead of Macro #97

Check out the new settings tab, if you are using a DualSense/DualShock4.

Author: Anna, Caitlyn
Name: Glamaholic
Description:
Create and save as many glamour plates as you want. Activate up to 15 of them
at once at the Glamour Dresser. Supports exporting and importing plates for
easy sharing.
Punchline: Save and swap your glamour plates.

Author: Shezwick
Name: Glamour Spam Remover
Description:
No settings needed, just add and forget.

Love linking plates to gearsets but hate all the chat spam when you swap? Here's your solution.
Punchline: What it says on the tin.

Author: DragonFlyy
Name: GlamourWishlist
Description: Create and manage lists of items that you want to save for glamouring later. Right-click context menus on items can be used to quickly add an item to a list.
Punchline: Create wish lists of items you want to glamour

Author: BitsOfAByte
Name: GoodFriend
Description:
A plugin to make improvements to the in-game friend system. Includes a client to communicate with the GoodFriend API to send & receive notifications with your friends.

Features:
- Private in design, no identifying information is ever sent about you over the network.
- Send & recieve notifications when your friends login and logout*.
- Get notified when your friends use the world visit system.
- Lots of filtering options for various events.

 * Requires friends to also have GoodFriend installed.
Punchline: Improvements to the in-game friend system! Send & receive login and logout notifications with friends and more!

Author: Kirrana
Name: High FPS Physics Fix
Description:
Causes the game's physics to work at higher FPS by making it update every few frames. 
Toggle with '/physics t', or use on/off instead of t. 
May cause excessive jiggling at lower FPS values. 
Disabling the entire plugin after turning on/off with /physics requires reboot to reenable.
Punchline: Reduces the refresh rate of movement physics, "fixing" it at high fps.

Author: Koenari
Name: Himbeertoni Raid Tool
Description: A collection of useful tools for RaidGroups, including loot management
Punchline: All you need for Raiding
Changelog: Bugfix: Lootmaster crashing and spamming log again

Author: Caraxi
Name: Honorific
Description: Assign custom titles to players.
Punchline: Customized titles for you and yours.

Author: Mistralsa
Name: Hotbar Backup
Description: Exports your current class hotbar into a JSON for backups. Allows imports from the same export on classes you don't have.
Punchline: Exports your current class hotbar into text. Allows imports too!

Author: KiwiKahawai
Name: Hotbar Helper
Description: Helps keep hotbars in sync with available actions. Particularly useful if you've lost your configuration, or transfer between platforms regularly.
Punchline: Keeps your hotbars up to date

Author: MidoriKami
Name: Hotbar Unlimited
Description: Allows you to move each individual hotbar slot to wherever you want, however you want.
Punchline: Total control over where to put your hotbar slots.

Author: MaryUsagi
Name: HUD Layout Helper
Description:
Allows you to use keyboard shortcuts in the HUD Layout Editor, like Ctrl+C and Ctrl+V to copy and paste the position of individual HUD elements, and Ctrl+Z and Ctrl+Y to undo and redo changes. 

Can also display an overlay showing alignment to other elements with Ctrl+R.
Punchline: Adds QoL features to the native HUD layout editor: Undo, Redo, Copy, Paste and alignment lines.

Author: nebel (prev. ascclemens, Necoji)
Name: HUD Manager
Description:
- Save infinite HUD layouts
- Edit your HUD with precision
- Automatically swap between HUD layouts based on conditions
- Make child layouts that only affect desired HUD elements
- Change visibility of job gauges
- Export and import layouts from text
Punchline: Take total control over your HUD.

Author: MidoriKami
Name: HUDUnlimited
Description: Allows you to modify any and all individual elements of the user interface to allow you to customize it however you wish.
Punchline: Total control of your User Interface.

Author: Infi
Name: Hunty
Description:
Never has it been that easy to finish your hunting log. 

+ List of monsters in the same location based on Rank
+ Clickable coords to open your map on that exact location
+ Clickable dungeon name to open your duty finder
+ Easy to switch between Grand Company and Jobs
+ Automatic selection based on current job
Punchline: Time to finish your log?

Author: Azure Gem
Name: I Hate Caps Lock
Description:
SORRY CAPS
Remove caps lock when pressing the Enter / Return key.
This plugin contains no configuration.
Punchline: Don't you hate CAPS LOCK so much?

Author: Infi
Name: Inspecto
Description: A simple plugin that keeps a history of people you inspected.
Punchline: Look back at that cute search comment even hours later~

Author: Critical_Impact
Name: Allagan Tools
Description:
Allagan Tool's primary purpose is to keep track of items across your characters/retainers/free company. With it's filter system you'll never lose track of items or not know where they should be sorted.

While this is it's primary purpose, it has quite an exhaustive list of other features including:
	- Craft planning
	- Market board integration
	- Item highlighting in inventories when searching/sorting and picking ingredients for crafts
	- Item window that includes vendor and source information among other things
	- Duty/mob/airship/submarine windows that are fully searchable
	- A filtering system that lets you setup complex searches for specific items 
	- Tooltip integration that'll let you see where the items are on hover
Punchline: Get organized in FFXIV, easily locate/show where to sort items, plan your crafting, and search for mobs, duties, airships, and submarines!

Author: Asriel
Name: Item Icons
Description: Display custom icons for items for easier inventory mangement.
Punchline: Works perfectly out of the box! Use /ii to configure.

Author: PunishedPineapple
Name: Item Use
Description: Displays indicators in the item help popup for when an item is used by leves, GC dailies, etc. to help you decide what is worth keeping, selling, or taking as a reward.
Punchline: Easily see common item uses.

Author: NightmareXIV
Name: JustBackup
Description: This plugin automatically backups your game and plugin configurations upon game/plugin starting.
Punchline: Automatically backup your game and plugin configuration.

Author: BitsOfAByte
Name: Kiko Guide
Description:
Comprehensive guides for duty content such as Dungeons, Trials and Alliance Raids.

Key features:
- Automatically open a guide when entering a duty
- Neat user interface that scales well at small sizes
- A short-text mode for easier reading & accessibility
- Anti-spoiler protections by default
- Built-in guide editor
- Integrations with your favourite plugins
& more to come!
Punchline: The ultimate guidebook for in-game duties, great for sprouts & doing your daily roulettes!

Author: Gotest
Name: Kingdom Hearts UI Bars
Description:
A plugin that makes Kingdom Hearts UI stuff, such as a health bar for the player.
If you have any questions, issues or suggestions, please post an issue in the github or ping me in the Discord!
Punchline: HP bar, MP bar, EXP bar, oh my!

Author: MidoriKami
Name: KitchenSync
Punchline: When level sync'd, make skills you don't have access to more transparent

Author: athene
Name: Launchpad Hotbars
Description: A plugin that allows you to map hotbar actions to a novation launchpad. /lphb to open config.
Punchline: A plugin that allows you to map hotbar actions to a novation launchpad

Author: grittyfrog
Name: Macro Mate
Description:
Macro Mate lets you store and run an unlimited number of macros. You can also bind macros to normal macro slots.

For example, you can:

- Automatically swap in the correct raid macro when you enter an instance
- Store longer macros and automatically split them across multiple macro slots.
- Use almost any icon in the game for your Macros
Punchline: Store and run an unlimited number of macros. Bind them to normal macro slots.

Author: Sylf
Name: Macro Recorded
Description: Records a crafting rotation you start and provides a way to export it to a macro so you can reutilize it.
Punchline: Want to record a crafting rotation and export it as a macro? Look no further!

Author: pinapelz
Name: Malmstone Calculator
Description:
Calculate the number of wins/losses needed in different modes of PVP before achieving your target Series Level.
Use /pmalm to get started
Punchline: Keep tabs on how much more PVP you have to play before unlocking your next Series Malmstone reward!

Author: Azure-Agst
Name: FATE/Map Gil Tracker
Description:
This plugin aims to simplify gil tracking for FCs who use FATEs/Maps as fundraising events!
Simply install it, enable it, and it'll automatically track every chest or sack opened and calculate how much gil each person owes.
Punchline: A Plugin to track gil earned from FATEs or Treasure Maps!

Author: SaMo
Name: Map Party Assist
Description: Tool for keeping track of treasure maps opened by party members and recording map and dungeon statistics.
Punchline: Treasure map tracker and statistics.

Author: MidoriKami
Name: Mappy
Description: Replaces the in-game map with an ImGui implementation with several additional features.
Punchline: A more versatile in-game map

Author: Zhyra
Name: Market Uploader
Description: Uploads market data to market.xivhub.org and other configurable aggregators.
Punchline: Uploads market data to market.xivhub.org and other configurable aggregators.

Author: Infi
Name: Easy MBHistory
Description: Copies the marketboard transaction history into your clipboard with configurable options.
Punchline: Useful for when you want to quickly export marketboard transaction history.

Author: MidoriKami
Name: Memory Marker
Description:
Ever forget which waymark slot holds your pre-fight positions? Which waymarks are for pugs and not your static?
Worry not! MemoryMarker has your back!

Loads and Saves waymarks when changing zones. Allows you to rename presets in the waymark window.
Punchline: Simple Waymark Management with Renaming Features

Author: NightmareXIV
Name: XIV Instant Messenger
Description:
Features:
- Opes a direct message window when you message someone or they message you
- Each window contains your DM chat with certain person
- Open and cycle through recent chats with a hotkey
- Execute emote commands on a player from their DM window without needing to manually target them
- Automatically record your chat log in an easy to read text file
- Fully customizable styles
Punchline: A direct message manager made in fashion of WoW Instant Messenger.

Author: daemitus, MidoriKami
Name: ezMiniCactpot
Description: This plugin highlights tiles and lines in MiniCactpot that represent the best potential action you can take.
Punchline: Shows the next best move in Mini Cactpot.

Author: JayceOfSpades
Name: Mini-Mappingway
Description: A plugin to show your friends and FC members on the minimap. Customise the markers and toggle whether you want to see friends, FC members, or both, in the settings! Icon by @Miendoodle on twitter. Thanks nya for the idea!
Punchline: A plugin to show your friends and FC members on the minimap

Author: Sylf
Name: Monster Loot Hunter
Description: Check where you can obtain a material from monsters, duties, crafting, gathering or where they can be bought from NPCs.
Punchline: Check where you can obtain materials.

Author: NotNite
Name: Moonbase Omega
Description: Plays chat messages sent in Cosmic Exploration via DECtalk (the TTS used in Moonbase Alpha).
Punchline: Adds Moonbase Alpha TTS when in Cosmic Exploration. aeiou!

Author: Samuelka
Name: Mount Collectioner
Description: A plugin allows you to track received mounts by character.
Punchline: Plugin for track collected mounts

Author: Jen Hyul
Name: Mount Radio/Mount Music Player
Description: /radiosettings, /radiotoggle, /radiovolume, /radioautostart, /radioautostop
Punchline: URL music player for your mounts! Stream internet radio when on a mount or on foot.

Author: 53m1k0l0n, Gotest
Name: Mouse Target Tooltip
Description: A plugin that shows a tooltip for mouseover targets.
Punchline: Shows a tooltip with a little information for characters that the mouse is over.

Author: kalilistic, karashiiro, shadow_kras
Name: NeatNoter
Description: NeatNoter allows you to take notes without switching windows or any of that.
Punchline: A note-taking plugin.

Author: Meisterlala
Name: Neko Fans
Description:
Shows you an image of a random neko character. Click on the image to view the next one.
You can choose different image sources, allowing you to look at Catboys, Waifus, Cats, Dogs and more.

Supported APIs:
Twitter, nekos.best, Nekos.life, Catboys, Dog CEO, The Cat API, Pic.re, Waifu.im, Waifu.pics and shibe.online

Warning: You might see naughty images
Punchline: Frustrated in a dungeon? Look at a cute cat girl!

Author: Kaminaris
Name: NextUIPlugin
Description: OverlayPlugin replacement for Dalamud, works similarly to BrowserHost with addition to having more options and built in websocket server.
Punchline: OverlayPlugin for Dalamud with built in HUD replacement

Author: Noevain,kalilistic, Anna
Name: NoSoliciting
Description:
Customisable chat and Party Finder filtering. In addition to letting
you filter anything from chat and PF, it comes with built-in filters
for the following:

- RMT (both gil and content)
- FC ads
- RP ads
- Phishing messages
- Static recruitment
- Trade ads
- Community ads
- Any PF with an item level over the max
Punchline: Adblock for FFXIV.

Author: MidoriKami
Name: NoTankYou
Description: Displays warnings when you or any party members are missing role specific actions such as partner buffs, pets, and tank stances.
Punchline: Warns you when yourself or others are missing role-specific actions

Author: NightmareXIV
Name: NotificationMaster
Description: Notifies you about various events while your game is minimized.
Punchline: Currently supports notifications: chat messages, approaching map flag, duty found, ending of cutscenes, gp restoration, error during logging in, mob has been pulled.

Author: Arcadia
Name: Ntfynder
Description: A plugin that uses Ntfy (https://ntfy.sh/) to send mobile push notifications when party members join or leave, or when a duty finder queue is initiated. Forked from PushyFinder.
Punchline: Mobile push notifications for the Party Finder. Alternative to PushyFinder without need for paid app or any hastle

Author: Mokocup
Name: Occult Crescent Helper
Description: Automatically notifies about FATE, CE or Aurora Mirage in Occult Crescent related content.
Punchline: Wake up baby, It's touch grass time

Author: Sl0nderman
Name: Ocean Fishin'
Description:
Automatically recommends bait to use based on your ocean fishing route. 
You'll get suggestions for spectral fish, fisher's intuition buff, and missions.
Punchline: Suggests bait for ocean fishing.

Author: NotNite, MidoriKami
Name: OfDungeonsDeep
Description:
Based loosely on DeepDungeonDex (by Strati), OfDungeonsDeep is an all-in-one tool for Deep Dungeon floor and mob information.
Data sourced with permission from https://www.ddcompendium.com/.
Punchline: Comprehensive monster dex for DeepDungeons

Author: darkarchon, KiwiKahawai
Name: Oh gee, CD
Description:
OGCD assistant providing Text To Speech, (Custom) Sound Effects and unlimited extra bars to visualize and alert you for your OGCDs.

This is an early version and things might still break.
Punchline: oGCD helper

Author: herulume, sevii
Name: OpenerCreator
Description: Create your opener and practice with a striking dummy. Provides basic analysis.
Punchline: Create, save, and practice your openers.

Author: InvoxiPlayGames
Name: Paggles
Description: Changes the time in the Server Bar to use the system locale for AM/PM designation.
Punchline: My Final Fantasy XIV says paggles right next to the time, what does this mean?

Author: shdwp, Avaflow, squidmade
Name: PartyIcons
Description:
Adjusts player nameplates base on current content. For example you can display raid positions (that are assigned automatically by listening to the chat), job icons, or names with job icons.

Reverse-engineering effort achived by authors of JobIcons: haplo, daemitus, Loskh, wozaiha, without them this plugin would not be possible!
Punchline: Replace names with job icons, raid role positions and more!

Author: pyrite_radio
Name: Party List Extras
Description: Adds Text and Icons next to the party list describing active buffs. Still missing some jobs - See github for progress. Please note the overlay goes to the left of your party list.
Punchline: Parses Buffs to help understand what your party is doing.

Author: Caraxi
Name: Party List Layout
Description: Customize the layout of the party list.
Punchline: Customize the layout of the party list.

Author: Zhyra
Name: PartyPlanner
Description: Browse community events sourced from partake.gg directly from your client!
Punchline: Browse community events sourced from partake.gg directly from your client!

Author: Rietty
Name: Party Sort+
Description: Sort your party list according to a series of rules built on top of the game's default system. Allowing you to specify based off Duty Instances and Jobs!
Punchline: Never worry about sorting your party again!

Author: Chirp
Name: Pathfinder
Description: A tool for visually locating any model path in the game world.
Punchline: Visualizer for nearby model paths. Adds +5 to perception.

Author: Glyceri
Name: Pet Nicknames
Description:
Give your minions, Carbuncles and Faeries cute nicknames
and share them with your friends.
Punchline:
Give your minions, Carbuncles and Faeries cute nicknames
and share them with your friends.

Author: Kurochi
Name: Pet Scale
Description: Adjust the scale of your own pets and other player's pets, independent of each other.
Punchline: Customize pet scale

Author: Tanker Tanker(aka Nvrnight)
Name: Party Finder Search Plugin
Description:
/pf
/pf on
/pf off

This plugin allows you to search for parties based on their descriptions. When you refresh the party finder, if any parties meet your search criteria, a notification sound will play and a link to each party will be displayed in the chat window.

This plugin will NOT automatically scan PF for you, it only runs additional search logic when you hit the refresh button.
Punchline: Find party finder groups easier.

Author: kalilistic
Name: PlayerTrack
Description:
PlayerTrack helps you keep a record of who you meet and the content you played together.
Organize players into categories, keep notes, and track them across name/world changes.
Customization options include colors, icons, nameplates, and alerts.
Punchline: Keep track of players you meet.

Author: Sevii
Name: Better Housing
Description: An improved housing experience. Furniture selection based on what you see, keybinds to switch modes and toggle counter and snap.
Punchline: Furniture selection that actually works properly

Author: SaMo
Name: PvP Tracker
Description: Record, browse and filter your Crystalline Conflict, Frontline and Rival Wings match history, view match scoreboards and view aggregated statistics like win rate and average damage dealt per match.
Punchline: PvP match history and stats tracker.

Author: QuackieMackie
Name: QuestJournal
Description: Quest Journal is a detailed quest tracker / viewer. Letting you see information about quest chains without using a wiki.
Punchline: See details about quests that the FFXIV doesn't tell you.

Author: Anna, Azure Gem
Name: Quest Map
Description:
Explore quests and their rewards.
- Search for quest names or their rewards, including instances,
  beast tribes, minions, etc.
- See an interactive map of quest requirements and unlocks.
- Open a quest info window even for quests you haven't completed.
- Open quest starting locations on the map or open quests in the journal.

Icons: treasure map by Anthony Ledoux from the Noun Project and
locked book by Anthony Ledoux from the Noun Project
Punchline: Explore quests and their rewards.

Author: Era
Name: Quest Share
Description: Follow your friends on their questing journey by seeing their progress through a shared quest. Provides markers for quest destinations and (soon) teleporting features.
Punchline: Share your quest progress with others.

Author: XorelCodes
Name: Quiet The Den
Description: Auto-mute BGM while in the Wolves' Den, because I've had enough and it ends here.
Punchline: Stop yer ears bleedin' in the Wolves' Den

Author: 53m1k0l0n, srkizer
Name: Quote of the Lobby
Description: Displays a random dialogue, and/or the datacenter you'll be connecting to when you press GAME START.
Punchline: Simmer does the light before every login.

Author: Abyeon
Name: Racingway
Description: A simple plugin for timing, logging, and ranking player times for your jumping puzzles!
Punchline: Time your jumping puzzles!

Author: Infi, PunishedPineapple
Name: Ready Check Helper
Description: Displays the names of the players that were not ready in chat following the completion of a ready check, and optionally adds ready check status icons over the party and alliance lists.
Punchline: Extends the game's built-in ready check.

Author: Cair
Name: Redirect
Description: Easily change the targeting priority for spells and abilities. Queue macros, sprint, and potions! Type /redirect to configure.
Punchline: Change where your actions are going, queue macros, queue sprint, and queue potions!

Author: Karou
Name: Render Adjust
Description: Allows you to dynamically adjust the in-game setting for rendered objects by FPS (and GPU Usage if you're on windows) and allows you to set a custom number of rendered objects manually. Uses GPU usage and FPS on Windows, and FPS only on Wine.
Punchline: Dynamically adjust your object rendering settings.

Author: Ibcrootbeer
Name: Retainer Alerts
Description: A simple plugin to remind you when your retainers are done with their ventures.
Punchline: Reminds you about retainer ventures.

Author: Populo
Name: Retainer Sales
Description: Quickly see which retainers have sold something while you were logged off.
Punchline: See retainer sales quicker

Author: Vielle Janlenoux
Name: RPP - Roleplay Profiles
Description: A plugin for Europe region roleplayers, displaying profiles from Chaos Archives (chaosarchives.org) for characters with the RP flag on.
Punchline: Display profiles from Chaos Archives (Europe region) in-game

Author: Meoiswa
Name: RPBlurb
Description: Realtime Roleplay sheets
Punchline: Realtime RP bios

Author: Kass
Name: RP Utils
Description: A suite (eventually) of features to support roleplay. Currently only the sonar. /rputils
Punchline: Supporting your RP needs.

Author: apetih
Name: RTyping
Description: Allows other people using this plugin to see your typing status when in the same party.
Punchline: Let people know when you r typing.

Author: Hattu
Name: SAMMI Webhook Plugin
Description:
Sends game data SAMMI via webhook, allowing users to automate OBS actions such as playing effects, transitions, sounds, etc. based on in-game events.
Requires SAMMI and OBS to function. See https://sammi.solutions or the plugin's readme on GitHub.
/psammi to configure.
Punchline: OBS automation based on game events via SAMMI webhooks

Author: ditzy
Name: Scout Helper
Description: A helper for generating scout tracker links for a-rank hunt trains
Punchline: A helper plugin for pre-populating hunt train scout tracker links

Author: Blooym
Name: Settings Enhanced
Description:
Settings Enhanced allows you to create zone-specific system and character configurations; For example, you could lower the amount of rendered players in Limsa, or mute other players sound effects while in stellar crafting zones. Your original configuration data is stored and automatically re-applies when entering an area with you have not created zone setting for, or when disabling the plugin/closing the game.

It is recommended that you create regular backups whilst using this plugin incase something does does break - upon install a check will be ran to see if at least one system/character configuration backup has been created; You will not be able to use the plugin if until you have created one.
Punchline: Per-zone system and character configurations

Author: ash
Name: Show Gear
Description:
Normally the Fitting Room defaults to showing you just the piece of gear you’re trying on. This plugin inverts that behaviour: when you launch the game, the Fitting Room (plus Item Dyeing and Glamour Plate Selection) will show all your gear by default.

NB: there are some oddities to how Item Dyeing and Glamour Plate Selection behave when this plugin is doing its thing. If you’d rather it not touch those windows at all, there’s an option for that (and more details about the problem) in the settings.

Icon adapted from OpenMoji, CC BY-SA 4.0.
Punchline: Shows your gear in the Fitting Room by default.

Author: Leon Aquitaine
Name: Sightseeingway
Description: Renames screenshots as they are created to include character name, map name, and coordinates. Monitors default, Reshade and GShade screenshots.
Punchline: Automatically rename your screenshots with character and location info.

Author: Elypha
Name: SimpleMarketBoard
Description:
You get some useful bonus info and a nice, condensed presentation. Might be useful for power users, perhaps?

Highlights:
  - Compact UI design
  - Cached search history
  - Flexible configuration
  - Live data filters
  - Colour highlights

Check out the Introduction in Plugin Configuration for general usage, and Github page for more details.

If you have any feedback or suggestions, feel free to contact me on Discord or Github. I'm always open to new ideas and improvements. Enjoy!
Punchline: The simple but ultimate market board plugin.

Author: Caraxi
Name: Simple Tweaks Plugin
Description:
A collection of Quality of Life tweaks. Aiming to improve the experience without changing anything drastically.
All changes are toggleable, with everything disabled by default. Visit the Repo for a full list of tweaks. (Globe icon below)
Punchline: This was supposed to be simple...

Author: Vielle Janlenoux
Name: Snooper
Description: Adds a /snooper command that shows a separate window that shows only messages from the player you're currently targeting. Useful for keeping track of different conversations during crowded RP events.
Punchline: See chat messages from your current target in a separate window.

Author: MidoriKami
Name: SortaKinda
Description: Sort your inventory however you want and keep it sorted.
Punchline: Total customization of your inventory

Author: rekyuu
Name: Stanley Parable XIV
Description: Check /narrator for full options or use /narratorvolume to set volume manually.
Punchline: Witty commentary to the brilliant things you do.

Author: Olaren
Name: Status Contrast
Description: You will finally be able to easily see the timer of your buffs/debuffs properly when the arena background is bright!
Punchline: Add contrast to your status icons

Author: Infi
Name: Submarine Tracker
Description:
+ Tracker for current builds, routes and times 
+ Builder to improve, solve builds and optimize EXP
+ Configurable notification for return and repairs 
+ Helpy filled useful information
+ Custom loot overview with history and export
+ Multiple overlays to help with daily tasks 
+ Supports multiple FCs
Punchline: You do not talk about Fight Club, same for Submarines

Author: karashiiro
Name: TextToTalk
Description: Chat and game dialogue TTS. Use /tttconfig to configure the enabled channels and triggers/exceptions.
Punchline: Chat and game dialogue TTS plugin.

Author: Berna, kai
Name: Hit it, Joe! (Formerly TF2-ish Critical Hits Plugin)
Description:
* Set sounds and flavor text to be played/shown whenever you deal direct or critical damage or heal.
* Set sounds to be played when a countdown is in progress.
* Use different configurations by job.
* Use the game's SFX or your own custom WAV or MP3 files.
Punchline: Configure sounds for critical and direct hits, plus some countdown music.

Author: Berna
Name: Team Fortress Fantasy
Description:
* Show a Win Panel (with sounds!) when you clear or get wiped in a duty.
* Show a TF2-style timer while in a duty.
* Enable the "Voice Lines" module (via /tfconfig) to have voice lines play when certain conditions are met. What conditions, you ask? It's a surprise! (Unless you uncheck the "Surprise me!" box.)
* More features maybe soon?

Note: This plugin uses files from a local Team Fortress 2 installation.
It'll search for the game's installation folder in all configured Steam Library Folders automatically.

Without a TF2 install, the Timer and Win Panel will work with FF XIV fonts, and no voice line will work.
Punchline:
[REQUIRES TF2 INSTALLED FOR MOST FEATURES] The Mann Brothers just found a deposit of gravel in Eorzea
and hired YOU, Mercenary of Light, to help them FIGHT for it.

Author: eja-git
Name: TheDot
Description: A dot to mark players hitbox
Punchline: A dot to mark players hitbox.

Author: Kurochi
Name: Tick Tracker
Description: Customizable bars that indicate the tick progress of HP/MP/GP regen
Punchline: Tracks the current tick for HP/MP/GP regen

Author: Nadya
Name: Tidy Chat
Description:
It is highly recommended to edit the default settings as you may disagree on which messages should be considered "spam"!

Provides granular filter options to filter nearly all game-related spam, leaving only important game messages in your chat.

  - Filters most spammy game messages
  - Blocks emote spam from other players
  - Condenses earned commendations into a single line
  - Shortens lengthy messages such as joining Novice Network or entering an instanced zone
  - Blocks repeated messages from appearing for a period of time
  - Automatically copies most 'with your chat mode in /say' quest dialogue to your clipboard
  - Write custom filters to Allow/Block messages!
  - And more!
Punchline: Better game messages and in-depth chat filters to keep a tidy chat.

Author: attick, perchbird & Speedas
Name: Title Edit
Description:
Create your own custom title or character select screen of your favorite location in-game, and open the game right up to that spot every time.
Includes a number of preinstalled title screens for you to use or get inspiration from, and an easy to use importer to use title screens that others have shared!
Character select supports recording your last visited location, per character display setting and even displaying yourself on a mount.
Punchline: Create, share, and shuffle custom title screens and character select screen for FFXIV.

Author: Liza Carvelli
Name: Title Roulette
Description: Allows you to pick any number of titles, setting a random one each time you use "/ptitle" or "/ptitle groupName".
Punchline: Pick titles you want in a title roulette.

Author: Stonewind
Name: Toastingway
Description: Displays new items, crystals, and gil as toasts.
Punchline: Keep on top of new items.

Author: Lore
Name: TooltipNotes
Description: Right-click any item in your inventory to start adding a note,or make a label in the config window to start adding your own labels
Punchline: A Plugin that lets you add notes to item Tooltips

Author: Anna, maintained by foophoof
Name: Tourist
Description:
Tourist adds a window to assist with the sightseeing log.

- Show when sightseeing log vistas are available
- Add markers for ARR vistas
- Open vista locations on your map
- Hide already completed or unavailable vistas
- Show the command needed for each vista

"sightseeing" icon by muhammad, from thenounproject.com CC BY 3.0
Punchline: Finish your sightseeing log.

Author: Infi
Name: Tracky Track
Description:
### Normal Functions 
+ Track currency increase
+ Track repair costs
+ Track teleport costs
+ Track result data for Desynthesis
+ Supports multiple characters

### Advanced  Functions
+ Track results for Bulk Desynthesis
+ Track rewards for Venture Coffers
+ Track rewards for Gacha Coffers
+ Track rewards for Eureka Bunny Coffers
Punchline: Tracking data is fun

Author: Una
Name: Umbra XIV
Description: Consolidates common UI elements and actions into a single uniform interface in the form of a set of highly customizable toolbars.
Punchline: Adds fully customizable toolbars and 3D world markers to the game.

Author: LittleNightmare
Name: Used Name
Description: A simple tool to record players' used names and nickname base on SocialList. Right click on the target to add/sub/check the used names and nickname.
Punchline: A simple tool to record players' used names and nickname

Author: mkalash
Name: Vanilla Hotbar Extender
Description: Allows you to use commands to save the actions in a hotbar and then load them into any other hotbar. Like the vanilla "/hotbar copy" command, but unlimited, without taking up other hotbars to save the actions.
Punchline: Save and load actions into hotbars without taking up extra job hotbars.

Author: Dragon
Name: Visibility
Description:
Allows you to hide players, pets, chocobos and minions.
Includes VoidList, which is a better blacklist.
Accessible via /pvis
More information available via /xlhelp
Punchline: Allows you to hide players, pets, chocobos and minions.

Author: Infi, PunishedPineapple
Name: Waymark Preset Plugin
Description: Allows you to save, edit, place, import, export, and preview an unlimited number of waymark presets.
Punchline: Improved Waymark Management

Author: PunishedPineapple
Name: Say What?
Description: Prints NPC speech bubbles to the chat log.  Please check the plugin settings and your chat log filters to make sure that they are compatible with each other.
Punchline: Persistent NPC Flavor Text

Author: cassandra308
Name: Where am I again?
Description: Shows what zone/region/territory you are in up in the corner next to the server and time info. Open config with /waia.
Punchline: Shows what zone/region/territory you are in next to the server info.

Author: Marethyu
Name: Where's my mouse
Description:
Add UI element on top of the mouse like circle to keep track of your mouse location during gameplay.
Open settings with /wmm
Punchline: Allows you to not lose track of your mouse on the screen

Author: Megurt
Name: Which Mount
Description: Plugin adds a 'Mount Search' button to the target's context menu, showing information in chat about the mount and how to obtain it. Settings allow you to include the current availability of the mount in the game and other details.
Punchline: Show mount information of other players

Author: BitsOfAByte
Name: Wholist
Description: Show which players are nearby to you, alike to World of Warcraft's "/who" command.
Punchline: Show which players are nearby to you, alike to World of Warcraft's "/who" command.

Author: perappu
Name: Who Said What Now
Description:
Chat history plugin, view history per character, per group, or search.
 Main command /whowhat
Punchline: Chat history plugin, view history per character, per group, or search.

Author: ash
Name: Who's Talking
Description:
Once installed, join a Discord voice channel and an XIV party, and have people put their character names in their Discord nicknames (or configure things manually in the plugin settings). You should get colourful outlines around the job icons on the party list: green for talking, blue for muted, red for deafened, and yellow for unknown name.

Note that you'll get a permission prompt mentioning "StreamKit Overlay" – this is expected.

Some icons by Google, Apache 2.0.
Punchline: See Discord voice activity indicators directly on your party list.

Author: daemitus, MidoriKami
Name: ezWondrousTails
Description: This plugin prints the probability of getting a row in Wondrous Tails to the in-game display along with the average probability of what would happen if you shuffled.
Punchline: Adds row probabilities to the Wondrous Tails display.

Author: Lady Defile
Name: Wordsmith
Description: Wordsmith is a text editor with roleplayers in mind. It automatically breaks your text up for easy copy/paste, has advanced features, spellcheck, and even a thesaurus.
Punchline: A roleplay thesaurus and scratch pad.

Author: Kaz Wolfe
Name: XIVDeck
Description:
This plugin allows players to use an Elgato Stream Deck as a virtual utility hot bar. Actions are called directly, meaning there is no need to set up awkward keybinds, custom macros, or any other settings.

Note that the XIVDeck Stream Deck plugin must also be installed for this plugin to be useful. You can download the Stream Deck plugin from the linked GitHub repository, under the "Releases" section.

Please report all problems to KazWolfe#2896 in the Dalamud Support server or by opening an Issue on GitHub.
Punchline: Turn your Elgato Stream Deck into a hotbar!

Author: Glyceri
Name: Fatal Frame
Description: Takes a screenshot upon death (and other events).
Punchline: Takes a screenshot upon death (and other events).

Author: darkarchon
Name: XIVJitterFix
Description:
With the release of 7.0 SquareEnix has implemented several temporal antialiasing solutions. However they all have a severe bug that affects image quality significantly.
This plugin will restore using jitter when talking to NPCs or in cutscenes and gpose. Jitter (not noticeable micromovements of the camera) is necessary for temporal antialiasing solutions (DLSS, DLAA, TSCMAA+jitter) to work properly.
For some reason, SquareEnix decided we don't need jitter during the time where the game benefits from using it the most.
Punchline: Fixes SquareEnix' botched antialiasing implementation

Name: XIVWindowResizer
Description:
Set your game window to arbitrary size not limited by your display resolution. Mostly useful for taking high-resolution screenshots without going fullscreen and using DSR/FSR.
